			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				About making money, well it takes a lot of time to get information about item/price etc. As the first posten mentioned how he traded and all the nice stuff he got. Well I am pretty sure if he had spent the time he played on leveling  he would be like in 40's in stead of 20's, and in higher lvl you have no worry about money anymore. I do a lot of trading to just for fun not really for the profit.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
About orc camps in EC, true you can sell DF belts for max 3pp per piece because these belts can be turned in in East FP for exp, faction and some gold. BUT, at lvl 10 there is NO WAY that you can solo the orc camp. There are two camps, orc camp 1 is bigger , has about 6-8  orcs with sometimes a named one with is about lvl 17 i think. You need a full group 10-15 to camp this and even so one wrong move can get you whole group killed, I have camped it many many times so I know what I am talking about. Orc camp 2 has about 4-5 orcs , much smaller and safer, can be camped by 4 players.<BR>
<BR>
To sell the belts for 3pp you need to have some patience but eventually you can find a buyer, be sure you carry at least 3 backpacks if you are about to camp orc camp1 coz you can have a full backpack of belts in 1.5 hour, respawn rate there is quite high. Good luck !<BR>

				</font>
